            <title>[LU-13628] sanityn test_106a test_106c: supported stx_attributes: got &apos;&apos;?&apos;&apos;, expected &apos;&apos;30&apos;&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13628</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for S Buisson &amp;lt;sbuisson@ddn.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/dde8990f-7243-4a60-8eb9-38494d02bad6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/dde8990f-7243-4a60-8eb9-38494d02bad6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_106c failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&apos;supported stx_attributes: got &apos;&apos;?&apos;&apos;, expected &apos;&apos;30&apos;&apos;&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that this new test, introduced by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/36674/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/36674/&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10934&quot; title=&quot;integrate statx() API with Lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10934&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10934&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: integrate statx() API with Lustre&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, has never passed Maloo (it was always skipped).&lt;/p&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanityn test_106c - &apos;supported stx_attributes: got &apos;&apos;?&apos;&apos;, expected &apos;&apos;30&apos;&apos;&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
